      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i noticed you mentioned rwanda and bosnia as successes, but those are usually cited as huge failures for the UN because they failed to stop the genocides. wouldn't a lot of historians argue that the whole structure of the UN is actually fundamentally broken and outdated for the way the world works now?",
